  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6592.54 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6580 (-8286.5M) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+11125.8M), dealers are caught in a critical amplification zone where they're forced to buy any dips toward 6580-6590 and sell rallies into 6605. The massive -13B total GEX in BREAKOUT regime means dealers will aggressively chase momentum in either direction, creating violent trending moves rather than mean reversion. Key battleground is the 6580-6605 range with multiple negative gamma strikes clustered below current spot that will fuel acceleration if breached.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect explosive moves as dealers amplify any breakout above 6605 or breakdown below 6580.",
